                            <comment id="477393" author="emoly.liu" created="Thu, 6 Nov 2025 09:14:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a look at code, I think the key problem for this requirement is when and how to change llog chunk size properly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;define LLOG_MAX_CHUNK_SIZE to limit llog chunk max size&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when: use lgh_last_idx to tell if it&apos;s time to change llog chunksize
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;when it approaches the bitmap limit(i.e. 80%), increase chunk size for the next llog file&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;when the utilization becomes lower, decrease the size correspondingly&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;how: since llog header size is relative small to chunk size, the growth factor to chunk size is almost same to bitmap size, the practical record capacity. Then, start with 2x?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
